# Risk-accepted vulnerability IDs — union of local Trivy scan on the
# pinned vendor tag and CI's Code Scanning alerts (Trivy DB refreshes
# between local and CI runs, so both sources are captured). Every
# entry is `Status:fixed` upstream; the vendor's artifact was
# compiled/packaged before the fix landed. Renovate opens a base-tag
# bump PR when the vendor ships a rebuilt release; clear the
# corresponding line here when the bump lands.
#
# Format:
#   <ID>  # expiry:YYYY-MM-DD  ticket:SEC-XXXX  reason:<short>

